.TH "tpm_cr50_i2c_read" 9 "tpm_cr50_i2c_read" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
tpm_cr50_i2c_read \- Read from TPM register.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" tpm_cr50_i2c_read
.BI "(struct tpm_chip *chip "  ","
.BI "u8 addr "  ","
.BI "u8 *buffer "  ","
.BI "size_t len "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "chip" 12
A TPM chip.
.IP "addr" 12
Register address to read from.
.IP "buffer" 12
Read destination, provided by caller.
.IP "len" 12
Number of bytes to read.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Sends the register address byte to the TPM, then waits until TPM
is ready via interrupt signal or timeout expiration, then 'len'
bytes are read from TPM response into the provided 'buffer'.
.SH "RETURN"
- 0:         Success.
- -errno:    A POSIX error code.
